column2: "Haaah, the soil's going to get even more messed up if we keep having to fight here."

"これ整えるのにどれだけ
時間かかったと思ってるのよ
ぶつくさ、ぶつくさ。"
"Excuse me, Marge?"
"Who the heck is Marge?! Don't abbreviate the name of the Divine Queen, blasphemer!"
"...So, what is it?"
"That Devil Castle didn't happen to be set up in advance, did it?"
"Of course not! The only Devil Castles we have are on the border. We can't afford to stick them around inside the country."
"If that's true then... That Devil Castle was summoned on the spot?"
"Wouldn't the Queen of Cuent be the one to ask about that? Just slapping them down without a summoner feels like cheating."
"No, that is far beyond even what we can do in Cuent."
"I would say that the Devil Castle just now... felt somehow different."
"Rather than being summoned..."
"It seemed more like it just... appeared?"
"The readings appeared out of nowhere. That's not how a normal summoning works at all."
"It just popped out of nowhere, with neither summoning nor summoner. How did this even happen?"
"Argh, whatever! It's those four villains anyways! They're just doing whatever they want with my country!"
"If there's a problem, just crush the source! Isn't that right, Queen of Cuent? So let's hurry up and take my country back!"
"R-right!"
"How can she act so high and mighty when she's not even doing anything to help?"
"It's only natural that I do. I am the Divine Queen, after all! If I'm not, then who would be?"
"Acting haughty is part of a Queen's duty. Never forget that, Queen of Cuent!"
"Right! Understood!"
"I really hope Harriet doesn't start taking after Marge... She'll probably be fine, I think."
